node.title: Choirs got a bad rap during COVID. So is it safe to sing again now?
node.description: From contemporary tunes to Christmas carols, group singing has many benefits, but how do we keep it all COVID-safe?

node.title: Hanna risks her life every time she does a show; here’s why she keeps performing
node.description: Hanna Cormick’s performances make moving statements about ableism and climate change. Now, she’s calling for artists to embrace fragility and change the way they make art.

node.title: 'We can meet and have a coffee': His question was followed by a solid beat of silence
node.description: The bloke said he was a fan and that's always very nice to hear. Yes, I'm sorry to say, the broadcaster's ego really is that close to the surface, writes Virginia Trioli.

node.title: Covid-19 lockdown highlights 'ridiculous' Pharmac rule for access to safe sex drug

node.title: Engines tested and take-off imminent for replica of one of Australia's most famous aeroplanes
node.description: A replica of Sir Charles Kingsford Smith's Southern Cross aeroplane is just months away from flying again after a 10 year restoration.

node.title: Food, fuel and cash in short supply as Solomon Islands civil unrest leaves trail of destruction
node.description: Riots, arson attacks and looting over three straight days of civil unrest leave the capital of Honiara short on food and essential services. This is what the crisis looks like on the ground.

node.title: As new COVID-19 variant hits South Africa, some locals listen to preachers doing research 'from the internet'
node.description: Experts say vaccination rates need to pick up to prevent the new variant spreading in South Africa, as some of its citizens take their lead from preachers relying on misinformation from the internet.

node.title: The Wandering Creativity of Sophie Taeuber-Arp

node.title: Merck says its antiviral pill is less effective in a final analysis.
node.description: The drug, molnupiravir, reduced the risk of hospitalization and death in high-risk Covid patients by 30 percent. An earlier analysis had found a 50 percent reduction.

node.title: Lauren Boebert Apologizes to Muslims for Ilhan Omar Comment, Calls It a 'Distraction'
node.description: "There are plenty of policy differences to focus on without this unnecessary distraction," the congresswoman tweeted on Friday.

node.title: Pat Cummins isn't perfect and he's happy that way

node.title: When No. 1 Is a Lot Better Than No. 2

node.title: Ralf Rangnick Will Manage Manchester United. For Now.

node.title: Expert says chronic fatigue syndrome sufferers should be exempt from Covid-19 vaccination

node.title: Western monarch butterflies are returning to California

node.title: New variant: UK adds African countries to 'red' quarantine list

node.title: ‘I Can’t Just Quit’

node.title: Firefighter Placed on Leave for Allegedly Using COVID Vaccine Mandate as Toilet Paper

node.title: House of Gucci is inspired by a true story of scandal, betrayal, ambition and ... murder

The true story behind it is almost unbelievable. Warning: spoilers for House of Gucci ahead.
